reviews.text:
I recently came from Melbourne to KK for just one night solely for dental work, including implants with Dr. Alex ‚Äî and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with the experience!

Everything was planned out before I arrived, which made the whole process really smooth and stress-free, especially since I was on an extremely tight schedule. Dr. Alex made it all happen within that short time, which was incredible. He is incredibly patient, knowledgeable, and takes the time to explain everything clearly ‚Äî I felt really well cared for from start to finish.

Big thanks to his lovely team as well ‚Äî everyone from the front desk to the assistants was so warm and welcoming, which made all the difference.

Also a special shoutout to Dr. Joanne for painting a few temporary teeth on my clear aligners so I could still smile confidently while waiting for my crowns. Such a thoughtful touch!

Highly recommend this clinic to anyone looking for professional, caring, and efficient dental care. Totally worth the trip!

reviews.name: Judd Harris
reviews.text: I recently visited Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre and had an exceptional experience. From the moment I walked in, the staff was welcoming and professional, making the check-in process smooth and easy. Dr. Joanne took the time to thoroughly explain my treatment options, I felt confident and comfortable knowing I was in good hands. The clinic itself is very clean, modern and calming, which made my visit feel more comfortable. I was also impressed with the clear aftercare instructions I received. Overall, my experience at Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre was excellent, and I would highly recommend them to anyone looking for high-quality dental care!

reviews.text: Got my teeth scaled and whitened here last october, they are still sparkling white as of today! Would highly recommend Dr Joanne. Very pleasant to talk to and made sure the whole process was painless and comfortable.

reviews.name: Simple Lean
reviews.text:
I once trusted Alex Lo completely‚Äîhaving been his patient from childhood through adulthood‚Äîbut my recent experiences have left me profoundly disappointed. It seems that his focus has shifted from patient care to profit. I now believe he is frequently shuttling between Australia and KK, obsessing over converting Malaysian Ringgit to Australian Dollars, which suggests that financial gain has overtaken his commitment to ethical treatment. Please do not compared aussie dollar to RM and thinking is so cheap in KK. Our cost of living is different!

During my most recent visit, he performed dental procedures without offering a proper explanation and even removed teeth without my informed consent. This breach of trust, after nearly 20 years of care, is not only disheartening but also unacceptable. There are many other capable and ethical dentists in KK who prioritize patients over profit, and I can no longer recommend his services.

Furthermore, I ask that no response to my review claim a lack of patient records or insist that I come to the clinic to ‚Äúwork it out.‚Äù This feedback comes purely from a long-term patient and is not from a competitor. We are simply your patients, and we expect accountability for the care we receive.

reviews.name: tay phoebe
reviews.text:
Our entire family visited this doctor after my daughter tested positive for Influenza A at a pediatric clinic two nights earlier, as we were all showing similar symptoms. Upon arrival, I informed the doctor about my daughter's Influenza A diagnosis and expressed concern that we might have contracted the same virus. However, the doctor dismissed this and insisted that we all had bacterial infections based on his observations. He also mentioned that the clinic did not have an Influenza test kit and proceeded to prescribe antibiotics for all of us.
Unfortunately, this incorrect treatment (antibiotics instead of antivirals for Influenza A) had serious consequences. My mother-in-law experienced severe nausea, vomiting, dizziness, and difficulty walking due to low oxygen levels in her blood. We had to rush her to the hospital, where she was tested, confirmed to have Influenza A, admitted, and treated appropriately. The doctor at the hospital advised us to immediately stop taking all the medication prescribed by this clinic.
While I understand that not all clinics stock Influenza test kits or antiviral medications, this does not justify prescribing incorrect treatments based solely on convenience or availability. Despite being informed of our confirmed Influenza A case, the doctor proceeded with an inappropriate course of treatment, which only worsened the situation. It would have been far more responsible to recommend that we first obtain a test kit before prescribing any medication.
